---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Foundation — Yahuah's Feast Calendar | Nazaryah"
  description="The mo'edim of Yahuah, the Hebrew word that names them, and Creation's calendar set against man's. Three foundational studies before the calendar mechanics."
>
  <main class="cf-index">

    <div class="cf-index-inner">

      <a href="/calendar" class="cf-index-back"><span class="arrow">←</span><span>Back to the Calendar</span></a>

      <header class="cf-index-header">
        <p class="cf-index-eyebrow">— Category I &middot; Foundation —</p>
        <h1 class="cf-index-title">The Foundation</h1>
        <p class="cf-index-subtitle">The mo'edim of Yahuah, the Hebrew word that names them, and Creation's calendar set against man's. Before any other category, these three.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="cf-studies-grid">

        <a href="/calendar/foundation/moedim-set-in-heavens" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 1</p>
          <h3>The Mo'edim Were Set in the Heavens</h3>
          <p>Genesis 1:14 hides the entire feast calendar inside the word translated "seasons." The mo'edim existed in creation's design before Sinai, before Israel, before any priest blew a trumpet — written in the sun, the moon, and the stars on day four.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/foundation/hebrew-word-moed" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 2</p>
          <h3>The Hebrew Word Mo'ed</h3>
          <p>Appointment, not holiday. Mo'ed (H4150) names a fixed time and a set meeting — the same word for Sarah's birth-time, the plague on Egypt, and the feasts of Leviticus 23. A divine appointment Yahuah scheduled and expects His people to keep.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/calendar/foundation/creation-vs-mans-calendar" class="cf-study">
          <p class="cf-study-num">Study 3</p>
          <h3>Creation's Calendar vs. Man's Calendar</h3>
          <p>Two calendars, two sources. One was set in the sun, moon, and stars on day four. The other was decreed by Caesars and popes, with months named for Janus, Mars, Maia, and days for Saturn, Woden, and Frigg. Every believer eventually has to choose.</p>
          <span class="cf-study-cta">Read the Study →</span>
        </a>

      </section>

    </div>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .cf-index {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e0905 0%, #1a110a 25%, #160f07 100%);
    color: #b8a584;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 4.5rem 1.5rem 6rem;
  }

  .cf-index-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Back link */
  .cf-index-back {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8a7855;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem 0.5rem 0.65rem;
    border: 1px solid #2a1a08;
    background: rgba(10, 6, 2, 0.4);
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s, padding 0.2s;
  }

  .cf-index-back:hover {
    color: #c9a961;
    border-color: #4a3218;
    padding-left: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cf-index-back .arrow { font-size: 1em; transition: transform 0.2s; }
  .cf-index-back:hover .arrow { transform: translateX(-3px); }

  /* Header */
  .cf-index-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .cf-index-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8a7855;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
  }

  .cf-index-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.025em;
    line-height: 1.12;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cf-index-subtitle {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #b8a584;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Study cards */
  .cf-studies-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cf-study {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    background: #1a110a;
    border: 1px solid rgba(180, 140, 80, 0.18);
    border-top: 3px solid #c9a961;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 2rem 1.6rem 1.6rem;
    transition: background 0.25s, border-color 0.25s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .cf-study:hover {
    background: #221710;
    border-color: rgba(200, 160, 100, 0.34);
    border-top-color: #d4a04a;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .cf-study-num {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.24em;
    color: #a88b4f;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cf-study h3 {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: 0.015em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cf-study > p {
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
    color: #b8a584;
    font-size: 0.96rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    flex: 1;
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
  }

  .cf-study-cta {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    color: #c9a961;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .cf-study:hover .cf-study-cta { color: #f0e0bf; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .cf-studies-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .cf-index { padding: 3rem 1.1rem 4rem; }
  }
</style>
